This paper deals with the problem of resource allocation in LTE-LAA small base stations (SBSs) in unlicensed spectrum. This problem is related to network optimization and wireless communication, which are subfields of computer science. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The proposed approach also involves the use of deep learning algorithms for modeling and prediction, which falls under the subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of a noncooperative game model for achieving fairness, which is related to game theory and optimization (cs.LG and cs.IT). Finally, the paper mentions the use of real data traces for simulation, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM).
